# Spec file structure (docs/specs/)

When creating or editing **feature-level** backend spec files in `docs/specs/`, the document must include all **10 sections** defined in [docs/specs/SPEC-TEMPLATE.md](docs/specs/SPEC-TEMPLATE.md):

1. Feature Overview  
2. Functional Requirements  
3. API Endpoints / Data Surface  
4. Database Schema  
5. Business Logic & Validation Rules  
6. Authentication & Authorization  
7. State & Workflow  
8. Error Handling  
9. External Integrations & Events  
10. Non-Functional Requirements  

- Use **N/A** or **See §X** where a section does not apply.  
- Keep existing content; reorganise under these section headers where possible.  
- Implementation guides (e.g. `implementation-guide-phase-*.md`) may follow a different structure; the template applies to feature specs such as `*-specifications.md` and `secure-dc-spec-v2.md`.
